    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1950-08-31T18:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1950-08-31T18:00:00-05:00" n="35"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d35">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">886A.2553/8–3150: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Embassy in London</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d35fn1">Repeated to Tehran as 391, Baghdad as 88, Jidda as
                        80, Moscow as 168, and Cairo as 174.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1950-08-31T19:00:00-04:00"
                            >August 31, 1950—7 p. m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1157. For <gloss target="#t_urinfo1">urinfo</gloss>, <gloss target="#t_SAG1"
                        >SAG</gloss> demanding complete renegotiation of 1933 <gloss
                        target="#t_Aramco1">Aramco</gloss> concession contract. <gloss
                        target="#t_Aramco1">Aramco</gloss> Board has authorized Pres Moore to
                    discuss renegotiation with <gloss target="#t_SAG1">SAG</gloss>. Revision
                    contemplated by <gloss target="#t_SAG1">SAG</gloss> cld be expected to have
                    obvious repercussions on other contracts in area, particularly since key issue
                    appears to be Saudi Arab demand for <pb facs="0098" n="76" xml:id="pg_76"/>
                    income tax for which co. might obtain US Treas tax credit. No <gloss
                        target="#t_NE1">NE</gloss> concessionnaire now pays local income taxes.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
